content: Mi hanno bloccato il conto dopo un anno che lo utilizzo davvero poco. In tutto ci ho fatto girare meno di 500 euro. Uso la carta solo per Pagare il parcheggio della mia auto. Rimango dell'idea che REVOLUT tratta meglio i suoi clienti e consiglio a tutti di abbandonare questa inutile e complicata piattaforma. In all, I made it run less than 500 euros. I only use the card to pay for parking my car. Virtually nothing and nothing.Today I find myself stuck for several days already. name: Szymon Skrabanek
title: App is OK, support is nonexistent. And they just proved me right.
content: The app itself is OK and very clear - from a technical perspective.Support, however, is almost nonexistent. First, I've had my incoming transfer frozen for 2 full days without any explanation whatsoever as to why this was done, even after asking multiple times on the chat. Just yesterday when I tried to pay for a car (signed the contract already, at an official dealership, no less!), This time I've not only got the transfer frozen, but my account was also "temporarily" suspended! And with all of this with hand-wavy vague language such as "security reasons", etc. I'd like to know what exactly triggered this and why I cannot pay for a car like a normal human being, thank you very much. After replying with full documentation (invoices, job contract, the works) within literally half an hour, I still haven't received a reply.If you freeze people's transfers and/or accounts with large amounts of money, you should be calling them immediately(!) to clarify, and not sit around for 2 days while people are effectively losing money (both freezes and the suspension are making me extend my rental, which is costly!).Don't bother calling their support line of course, I've waited over 20 minutes for an "average waiting time of 5 minutes" only to hear that all support staff is currently unavailable - frustrating! Tried calling several times, to no avail.EDIT: More hand-wavy language in Monese's response. Yes, I know what the terms are, I know what the limits are (and I haven't even come close to those limits!). What I don't know is why there is a 2-day "review" period.Also, do you even read the reviews? I just wrote that I've sent you all of the details and probably more than I was comfortable with sharing (company finances) within 30 minutes of receiving your notification-of-suspension email.If I get a response email from your "support" today then I'll gladly consider changing the review or deleting it to let you save face. Otherwise, the review stands as-is.

content: I have been using a Monese account for about two weeks and the experience has been pretty horrendous. I wanted to top-up my card so I googled how to do it. I literally tried 6 different locations and none of them was able to do this for me. Two of them kept trying and eventually needed to refund me as the machine was not accepting my card or whatever. The rest would not even bother. I wasted so much time with this and it was extremely frustrating. So I went on the internet again trying to see if there was any other way to top-up my card. I found out I could use a Post Office. Finally, someone was able to do this for me only to find out later that it takes a whole day to appear in my account and that they charged me 5 pounds for it. Later I discovered that I can top-up my card with a maximum of 200 pounds per month. I understand this is my fault for not being aware of it but the experience with this was absolutely ridiculous!!! I am going to close this account as soon as I can and I do not recommend this bank to anybody at all!!

name: Balazs Simon
title: I started using Monese because it was‚Ä¶
content: I started using Monese because it was the first 'bank' in my country that allowed me to use Apple Pay. Luckily my real bank is now supporting Apple Pay, so I only use Monese whenever I'm abroad or making an international bank transfer because it has lower fees. However, my last transaction made me lose my faith in Monese and will probably never use it again. I'll keep Revolut for the same purposes that I used Monese. My issue all started on 1st Oct. I tried to transfer a few hundred pounds to my bank account from my Monese balance. However, the transaction was still not confirmed on the 4th so I decided to ask the customer service. (I have had a Plus plan for 6-7 months now and still active.) The days went by and I still didn't hear about Monese until the 10th. It took them 6 days just to issue a premium customer's issue. How could anyone trust them with their funds when they take so long with addressing issues.
reply: Hello, Balazs,We are extremely sorry to hear about the negative experience. The reason your payment wasn't cleared immediately is that we have to run checks every now and then to make sure that our service is safe to use for everyone. These checks are compulsory and in line with industry standards as set by our regulator. We appreciate your patience while our payments team manually verified it. We sincerely apologise for the inconvenience caused to you by this situation. We're very sorry to hear you are unhappy with our service, especially with the response times from our support team. We take this feedback very seriously and are currently looking into your situation.All the best,The Monese Team

name: Tania-Baglady Edwards
title: Slow to set up account yet it says it can be opened in minutes
content: After downloading the app and setting up the account I was prompted to make video call to finish the verification process. This was probably down to their poor automated system not being able to read my photo ID. Yet I made sure the camera shot was clear enough to be able to read before I submitted it. Perhaps they needed glasses and tried to read without them! I was told that I would receive an email link within the next business day which should have been on a Tuesday as I called on the Saturday and it was over the bank holiday weekend. I still have not heard anything more. When I log on to my account all I get is a message saying that they have to manually verify my details. And would take up to one business day! But they were verified over the video call in the end! What was the automated system all about then? The app is also a waste of time and space. Wasting phone memory as well! So Im uninstalling the app now because it is absolutely useless. Two days have passed and I had to send email to check it up. Still no reply. However after reading some of the bad comments about people being robbed and having their accounts blocked, I think I may have had a lucky escape so I wont be using them now if I do get the chance. Absolutely diabolical. I have opened accounts with Starling and Monzo and they are great. Use them instead. You still have to upload ID but their accounts are opened up in minutes. No hassle. Plus transfers are quick. You can use the app straight away before the card is in the post. And their cards come almost straight away! Unlike Monese. They are a real shambles. Somehow I don't trust them. I think they could be scammers
reply: Hello, Tania,We'd like to offer our sincerest apologies for any inconvenience we may have caused you. In certain cases the verification procedure requires manual intervention, which appears to be the case here. We are happy to see that your account was opened successfully with only a small delay, however we are still sad to hear that things didn't go down as you expected this is not by any means reflective of our standards of service and customer satisfaction.We take every feedback seriously and make necessary improvements for better user experience. We thank you for your patience!All the best,The Monese Team

name: Holger
title: Mobile first, easy to use, design heavy
content: Initial sign up was done using a promo code to receive a little bonus.After initial account creation, I needed to go through the usual validation procedure, which was, to my delight, easy and without leaving the app or having to do a phone interview. The app itself is functional, although too white in my Opinion (not a fan of sudden flashlight in my face in the evening) and at times too 'cutesie'.However, it's just an app and nonetheless has all functions, whistles, and bells I would expect from fintechs. Topping up can be done in a variety of ways, so no complaints there. Monese Hub isnt worth talking about quite yet, hopefully it expands in the future. Only having a British (SEPA enabled) account isn't great if your living elsewhere, as most people or companies distrust foreign accounts somewhat. Paying isn't a problem due to using the Mastercard network.Currently, only Apple Pay seems to work here, making it less convenient than other offerings as Apple barely reaches 20% market share.The card looks quite unique if that's your jam.Activation is easy, after arrival of the letter you only need to enter the code and it's ready to go. Sending money was straight forward,everyone who can use a phone should be able to do it. Now, however, my only real gripe:Tried contacting the support team, first one in the morning during office times, no answer as of yet(3days), same for another try yesterday. Just an overly cutesie and unhelpful bot that it was send to the service team as answer.I have to admit that it is nothing important overall, I would therefor refrain from removing  a point. We'll see what happens. Overall:If you want a prepaid card with modern, smartphone only focus, you can't go wrong with Monese.
reply: Hello Holger!Thank you for your honest review and feedback. We appreciate it!Our support team always reply as soon as they can, we apologise for any delays you might have experienced. name: pks
title: Great value for money and functionality
content: Would have been a 5 star review if their support wasn't so slow. Unless you are on the ¬£15/month tier you don't get priority support which apparently means waiting days for your enquiry to be answered. That is quite troubling, this is a bank and it has my money, support shouldn't be tiered or slow.For me personally, monese has more room to grow, but for the moment it's the best option (for my situation, your mileage may vary). I live and work in the UK but will be going abroad for a year or two and in that time will be working remotely for my UK employer, which means I'll be left with no UK address (as I rent) and thus no UK bank account as my (now previous) bank requires a UK address. I tried to switch to their International account, but that requires an income of ¬£50k a year and an address abroad... except those in the EU, those don't qualify for International account because logic and that is where I'm going. So I was forced to look for alternatives and settled for Monese because it has very low fees when spending or transferring money abroad, both GBP and Euro account, Apple/Google Pay, support for Direct Debits and Standing Orders, and an amazing mobile app that lets you control your account, open new ones, lock your card, etc. Basically it has everything that I need, for free or ... actually, it's always free. I'm staying on the free tier at the moment but when I go abroad and need to convert my GBP salary into the local currency the savings from the amazing monese exchange rate are much bigger than the cost of the monthly fee to get extra benefits like cheaper exchange. Checkout the current exchange rate on the monese website and what local exchanges and your bank offer - even if you are just going on a week or two holiday abroad, chances are it will be cheaper to upgrade for a month to one of the monese paid tiers (if you need the higher fee-free spending limits) and exchange/spend through them than use your bank's or local currency exchange office.
reply: Hi there!Thank you for such an honest and kind review! It means a lot to us :)Your feedback regarding the waiting time for an answer from our Support team will be raised internally, thanks for sharing your thoughts with us. Our Support team always does their best to reply as soon as possible, we apologize if you faced any delays.All the best,The Monese Team

title: Ruining your business
content: I had a terrible experience with Monese, while trying to use it as a bank for my digital marketing business. They were able to receive all the funds to my account, but when I tried transfering it to my other account it suddenly has been blocked. They sent me an email asking additional information about my business, which I did literally 10 minutes after receiving my email about account suspension. No answer for over a week, my funds being withheld, and when calling support, they couldn't provide me any information on how long the process might take. I have collected money from my customers to order products, but couldn't use them, since they are being withheld by Monese, therefore leading to refund requests and basically ruining my business. Definitely not recommend using Monese, since you don't know when you will become a prisoner of theirs.

title: Everybody be careful
content: Everybody be careful. If you add money using top up function, Monese stores your bank card's number for an indefinite period of time. Even if you remove your card from your account, they will keep it in their database.To test if this assertion is valid is really simple. You 'll need to Monese accounts though. First add some money using a bank card to your first monese account. Then remove the card. Then go to i.e. your wife's monese account and try adding the same card for top up. Monese will reject the request saying the card belongs to another user. How can they know ? The first user has already removed the card. I have requested exaplanation to this security threat but they gave answers to my emails once every week and their answers were out of scope. Can't trust them

name: Robert Noreiko
title: Helpless customer service (updated)
content: Helpless customer serviceIt has been number of weeks now or even months since I have started contacting Customer service of Monese to activate my Apple Pay. I am from Denmark, but for the summer time I am residing in Lithuania. There was no problem when I needed to activate apple pay on my iphone at first, just called the number stated in my Wallet and it was done. Then after some time I wanted to do the same on my watch. Same procedure. Called them again and I suppose it went to compliance as they started to ask me documents confirming my residence in Denmark, documents were uploaded, but activation was refused explaining to me that it is not available in Lithuania, okay, but I don't reside here, and everything they have asked to prove this was given to them, all they told me is to contact them when I am back to DK. Now, apparently Apple Pay became available in Eastern Europe countries. So iphone still asked to do the same thing. I have called them again several weeks ago. CS told me I will get a call back from their manager who activates Apple Pay same day. No one called. I called them again next day. Same story, apologies and manager will call me back same day for sure. No one called. I called again next day, said that no one calling me, they explained that I will get a call at some point as they are changing their system. Weeks later - today I called and spoke with Michael who clearly didn't sound happy but more like  annoyed because I am trying to activate Apple Pay, just following instructions saying on my iPhone. What he told me that I will get a call later. Then I explained him that exactly same thing 3 colleagues before were telling to me. And apparently he told me that system is getting change, and I am not getting a call today. So why even starting this conversation when CS knows that no one is going to call me back. Then I asked estimated time, he said he can't give any time, or in other words felt like he just wants to get rid of customer calling him. No apologies no nothing. Fine. Prefer not to call Customer service as it leads nowhere. Just waste of time on waiting line and no solutions.UPDATE:Several days after leaving negative one star review I have been contacted by one of supervisors. Can‚Äôt describe how polite and helpful he was, first thing he helped me with is activating Apple Pay that I waited for so long! It was great experience speaking to him and finding a solution. This could have been done in the very beginning, not when customer leaves negative review. Therefor I am leaving 4 stars, as customer service specialists didn‚Äôt help me, but their supervisor did, which is great! I was not left ignored but helped!Kind regards

You must have received a detailed email regarding your situation, explaining the dispute procedure and as we can see, you have been in contact with our team regarding this. name: Paulo Dias
title: Account closure and funds not returned
content: Hello. I would like to report an issue that is a Public matter.I was living in Slovakia and I got a job in the U.K. The contract was signed off at the end of April to start at the beginning of June.As I didn‚Äôt have an UK bank account at that time I decided to open a Monese Bank account (end of April) so my new company could transfer their relocation support allowance to me.The process to open the bank account was quick. It was not needed an UK address so I decided for Monese as I didnt have yet an UK address at that time and Monese Banking do not requires it.I got my relocation allowance transfered into Monese account and also requested a debit card.On the 31.05.19 I finally moved in to the UK and started to use the Monese account and cards to make payments, set up first direct debits and the standing order to pay my property letting.Also I have topped up the Monese account by transfering money from my Portuguese Bank account when was necessary ( I am from Portugal).On the 27.06.19 I got my first UK salary transfered to this Monese account and on the next day (28.06) I had the standing order to pay my letting and a direct debit as well. On Friday, the 28th of June I was in Slovakia for a long weekend break and I tried to make a payment and to get cash and both operations were denied. I thought something was wrong with using the card in Slovakia so I contacted the Monese support team. I didn‚Äôt get an answer as why this was happening.Later on that day when I was taking a look at my emails I found an email from Monese as copied below:‚ÄúWe just need to let you know that we‚Äôve completed all the checks that we‚Äôre required to perform in order to keep your account open.Unfortunately, because we couldn‚Äôt gather enough information, your account will now be closed.We‚Äôd like to give you some idea as to why we‚Äôre unable to continue servicing your account at this time.At Monese, we need to make sure that the use of your Monese account is compliant with certain legal requirements as issued by our regulator, the UK Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). These are rules that we are required to follow in order to¬†service you as a customer.At this time, we haven‚Äôt been able to verify that your account activity falls in line with these FCA rules.Please note that we‚Äôre now unable to provide you with financial statements and we‚Äôre unable to reopen your account.In addition, any Direct Debits, payrolls or subscriptions linked to your account will be discontinued due to closure of your account. If funds have recently been transferred to your account but have not yet arrived, they will be returned to the sender.You currently have ¬£Xxxx.xx in account no. Yyyyy.Unfortunately, the source account from which these funds were paid is unable to receive returned transfers. In order to return the funds, we require you to provide us with the details of another account of which you are the account holder‚ÄùSince then I called to Monese support line where they told me they cannot assist with the issue as they deal only with superficial issues (?).As it was requested on their email and then confirmed by Online Support Advisors I have replied to the email requesting (again) more information as why account was closed without any warning and I have provided them with alternative account details so they can return my funds back to me, I asked for an estimation date to when my funds would be transfered and available for me. And the result is that I Still have no answer!!!!Luckily I had another account with funds available so I can have cash to make my normal life on a daily basis but I had to transfer money from my savings, transfer money from Portugal to UK to pay my letting agreement, direct debit that was supposed to be paid and was not!! So far I do not have any reply to my emails and phone calls. What if this happens to someone who does not have any other funds available and have to pay bills, buy food, is currently travelling, etc.??I have read now in some reviews that this situation happened several times and people are complaining they still haven‚Äôt got their money back after 5 months.How can this situation happen without any respect for Customers and without an action from whom is responsible to regulate these issues?I look forward to receiving any type of assistance and guidance to solve my issue asap, get my funds back, complain about the issue by reporting it to the right official organisation and get a compensation for all the mess created in my life over the last days and additional expenses I had because of it. Also as a Public matter I‚Äôd like to avoid this situation to others.
reply: Hello, Paulo,We are very sorry to hear about your negative experience. Please be advised that we only close accounts if your account usage is not in accordance with our Terms and Conditions sections 14&15. We are glad to see the remaining funds have been transferred but we sincerely apologise for any and all inconvenience this situation must have caused you.Thank you for your understanding.All the best,The Monese Team

title: Good but could be better
content: Very easy set up and card arrived within a few days (almost a week earlier than the initial email said it would). Love the fact I can have a GBP account as well as the option for a Euro account if I go travelling around Europe. My only negatives: the length of time most payments take to be completed... on the two occasions I have used the card in store (for very small amounts I should add - like 0.50p) sits under ‚Äúpending‚Äù for over a day. Likewise transferring funds from my Monese to my other bank account takes a very long time compared to other banks I‚Äôm with.Also being charged to deposit cash in to my account seems a bit unfair. You opened a personal account based on this information.As is my right, my registered and correspondence address are not my residential address on companies house. Companies house is a publicly accessible site and I simply (like many others) do not wish to have this information available to the general public.There is nothing you could not verify by requesting further information.

If your card issuer does not participate in the mentioned schemes, the card top up may fail.Apart from that, other common reasons are that you may have entered incorrect card details (expiry, CVV/CVC, name on card), insufficient funds, or you may have exceeded the daily or monthly top-up limit set by your card issuer.PS! Credit cards and AMEX cards cannot be used to top-up your Monese account. The card that you top up with, needs to be either a MasterCard or a Visa debit card.If this message doesn't answer your question please contact us from your registered email, so we can look on your issue further. name: Jonathan Lester
title: Monese on-line bank account with free debit card
content: Excellent on-line bank account which is very easy to apply for .....on your mobile app is clear and easy to use. Free debit chip and PIN contactless equipped card arrived super fast (in just 2 days!).Your card can be used to pay for goods/services in all shops that accept Mastercard. Can also use to pay for things on-line and via telephone. You can also draw cash from ATM's. Very easy to top-up/load your card with funds. Cash top-up's can be made at Post Offices and via Paypoints. Many extra convenient features within the mobile app which only you can access via a PIN style security code which you set yourself.There are currently 3 types of plans to suit everyone - Starter, Plus and Premium. Simply choose the one you feel would suit you best.Multi level security is superb and you also have the ability to Block and Unblock your card instantly via the mobile app (should you lose or misplace your card).This type of account is the convenient trend of modern digital money and very secure. All your transactions are also displayed within the app for you from top-up's to expenditure and is in Real Time except top-up's paid in at the Post Office which will show on the morning of the next working day (Paypoint cash top-ups are instant)All in all this is a good all-rounder which would particularly suit those who otherwise find it difficult to open a conventional high street bank account. No credit checks required. Only proof of ID which you complete very easily within the mobile app using your mobile's camera, which is completed super fast !I would give Monese more than 5 STARS if there were more !!....... well done Monese ! Extremely happy with your service :-) :-)
reply: Hi Jonathan, Thank you for your comprehensive review and your feedback! We're happy having you, and we will pass it along to the team! ü§©Yours, The Monese Team

name: Marcus Richert
title: Poor support and IBAN/SEPA does not work as advertised
content: I really liked Monese up until about a month ago when I realized their support sucks badly when you need them for anything more advanced then using the debit card to buy stuff. They bounce you between people who just ask you to repeat your issue again and refuse to read the previous transcript (that explains exactly what the issue is) even when prompted and don't respond until you've copied and pasted it one more time... and then they still don't have the chops to resolve the problem. I've had problems making a simple SEPA payment for more than a month. They told me my BIC code was wrong (though the app tells you you should actually be able to leave this line blank!) and asked me to talk to the receiving bank because they should have a different, shorter code. I actually went to one of said bank's offices and they looked at me as if I were an alien - "No, we only have one BIC code, you have the correct one, this is how the system works, and you shouldn't even need one to make an IBAN payment". I ended up forced to make the payment with my traditional bank at a much higher cost, which is really ridiculous as I'm paying Monese ¬£5/month precisely because they're supposed to be able to do stuff like this for a much cheaper price! It's been a total letdown. They are not a reliable replacement for your traditional bank. Buyer beware.
reply: Hello, Marcus,We are very sad to see you had to leave this review. After reviewing the situation, the assistance you received was not as helpful nor efficient as it should have been be.  We take this kind of feedback very seriously and this matter has been investigated to make necessary improvements for better user experience. We sincerely apologise again for the mistakes we made and for the frustration this understandably caused you. Thank you for your patience!Sincerely,The Monese Team

I read some negative comments from viewers were denied to have business account and they were not informed why. Actually this is should not be a negative comment and it sends out a message that Monese do the home work before they welcome a client to have a business account and they don‚Äôt accept anyone just to have the monthly fees or to increase the number of clients. Right now, my entire experience with Monese is very positive and I highly recommend them for your both private and business use.

name: Selma Aydemir
title: Monese! Please read it before you trust them with your money!!!
content: I‚Äôd like to share my experience with monese with you so you decide to trust them with your money or STAY AWAY‚ÄºÔ∏è‚õîÔ∏è‚õîÔ∏è‚õîÔ∏èOn Friday 10th, May 2019, I made a standing order to a lettings agency for my new flat that I intended to move in on 13 May 2019. When I made the standing order using monese app, there was a message on my screen, saying that the transaction will be cleared on Monday 13. I made all the arrangements according to that message. I took a day off, packed my stuff, organised removal company, talked to the agent, made an appointment to collect the keys and made sure everything is in place for Monday 13th. Then to my surprise, I received an email from monese at 08:59 in the morning asking to provide documents ie: payslips, invoices, emails which I provided immediately. Then I went on the app and went through support section to make sure that they got all the necessary documents and it is very URGENT for them to view my mail and made the transaction. 9 hrs passed and still my messages haven‚Äôt been read!!!Removal company arrived, collected belongings at the arranged time but still no news from the transaction. I started making phone calls. First phone call I made, I was told to provide further documents that they were not mentioned in the first email. I then provided further documents they asked for. Still no news even though I explained the urgency of the situation. Then I started making phone calls, to see where I am in the process. Each time all I got was that my mails were forwarded to a specialist team. Meanwhile time was ticking, removal company was wanting to unload the van, lettings agency calling me, I am running out of time. Making several very frustrating phone calls, I still have no results. Messages not been seen, let alone answered. They are not giving me any indication of time when it is going to be solved or why this is happening other than telling me that they have random checks and it is going to resolve.I am now left with no home to go this evening, removal company charging for every hour, lettings agency wanting to know when the money will be cleared and monese‚Äôs specialist team is still checking my mails...I have never ever experienced such appalling services in my entire life. I cannot see the money in my account, neither it went to agency‚Äôs bank account. If I knew such banking services will be so inefficient and so incompetent customer services, then I will never ever look at banking system like MONESE!!!I strongly recommend TO STAY AWAY!
reply: Hello, Selma,We are extremely sorry to read about the situation you were in. We apologise for the frustration caused to you in the result of your account closure. In situations like these, where further verification is necessary, our team needs time to manually check the information provided and our compliance team must follow certain protocols to ensure the safety and security of all user‚Äôs account as well as our system. We are glad to see the situation has been solved, however we would still like to extend our sincerest apologies for the inconveniences.All the best,The Monese Team

The fca told be to demand what law they were using in order to require me to give highly private info. This is none of there business thats a ref number of a conversation between me and the regulator. It is private.They have now locked my account effectively seizing my money leaving me unable to buy food.Do not under any circumstances deal with these people. They are not a bank according g the the FCA they arnt even the organisation that they gave licenced to operate in fact they act as an agent on behalf of the licenced company.

We apologise if you felt this was in any way intrusive to you. You must have also received a message from our team regarding the release of the funds on your account. name: Alexandra
title: My account Monese was blocked
content: I opened an account with Monese last year. The mobile app is easy to use, very friendly (and to be honest) a mobile bank always at hand. I did not have any problems with Monese until last month when I received a notification as my account is blocked . I was contacted by the Customer Service, who were friendly and explained to me their procedure and why blocking an account, and after that I received email from Compliance Team, who were also very friendly and explained the steps to follow to unlock my account.Now I'm waiting for an answer from them if my account will be unlocked or the account will be closed ( really I don't want my account to be closed :) ) if they decide to close my account, I know I have no reason to worry about the amounts left on my account  (Approximate amount of 9500GBP) because I'm sure they are honest and respect the terms and conditions - Their responsibility towards clients - Sections 17 ''17.1.6 In all other situations of default, our liability will be limited to the return of the Available Balance.''I can not blame anyone for blocking my Monese account because I know a procedure is being followed under the terms and conditions set by the financial institution, These being said, you may be wondering why I rated 5 stars Monese .Well, because I received the necessary information in a timely manner regarding the blocking of account as well I was informed in time concerning any update on this issue.--23.04.2019 - Well sadly, I came back to tell that, my Monese account was closed . Today I received an email notification as the account with them was unfortunately closed .As far as I know, procedure of refund of the remaining amount in account  may take up to 30 days.I still do not change my 5 star rating ! :)*I will return to inform you when the refund will be complete .

name: steven williams
title: IN BREACH OF TERMS AND CONDITIONS
content: I opened an account with Monese and realised that the account wasn't what I had expected. I tried to return money back to my account that I  transferred money from and instead transferred the funds to a Euro monese account by mistake I accept there are currency conversion charges in this type of transaction,  I then realised the correct procedure to transfer the funds to my origin bank account and requested transfer. This was declined two days later, in between this period of time I spoke to an advisor via chat and explained the whole situation and I asked if I could get the funds back to my origin bank account and he said there was nothing he could do? and said I would have to raise it with head office. I also phoned Monese and spoke to an advisor they also said they cannot help! Regarding the initial chat with Monese I have received a copy of the conversation several times via e mail there is no personal communication regarding my initial request.  The e mail I sent to customer services was to request termination of my account with immediate effect and the funds returned to my account. Accorrding  to monese terms and conditions a person can do this at any time. So Monese you are in breach of your terms which are contractual!  My next course of action is to report this to visa and the financial Ombudsman. And I would advise anyone looking to bank with Monese to think carefully they may have excellent reviews but these relate to banking and ease of use. When it comes to support and help when things go wrong it seems there is none or they are reluctant to give it! I am thoroughly disgusted with their lack of support in these circumstances

I tried everything to help the person on the other end of the phone at monese support understand, but they didnt and they went as far as saying " you log onto the system and try and find the payment then". I pay the middle fee, but if seems unless you pay the highest fee noone from support gives a damn. I emailed them via the app and still 6 hours later I havent had a response, so I ended up having to phone them. I was on hold for 20 mins waiting for them to answer the phone. title: Easy to open and great app... But
content: Really easy to open a account and delivery of the debit card was swift, but unfortunately came across a issue when trying to load a large amount onto the card, amount was accepted but subsequently card was blocked, got in contact with CS who were a friendly bunch in Rochdale but even after passing all the details of the source of funds my account was closed due to falling foul of account opening rules (I'm a British citizen with a property in the uk and pay tax in the uk, whilst also having a property abroad) the document team were friendly enough and promptly refunded my account balance back to me once I provided them with bank details (can't fault their speed of service) , in the time I was using them I couldn't fault them and its a shame they closed my account, overall a good bank with a great app but if large transactions are involved it looks like they would prefer to close accounts rather than prove to the CFA that the account and source of funds were legitimate. Have since moved to a competitor and have been proactive and mentioned source of funds, upto now no problems, maybe should have mentioned to monese before I sent the transfer. Overall I think a good bank when dealing with smaller day to day transactions

name: W A Brotherston
title: Most of the experience is positive BUT
content: Following my 2 star review (see below) I received a telephone call from Monese Support.  They are clearly concerned about my review as they should be and promised that the situation I faced will not recur.In other aspects of the service I have received I would give a 5 star rating.  Following the telephone conversation and assurances I have received I revise the rating to 4 star because of the positive nature of the telephone call and the fact that they reacted.  But not yet 5 star until I am happy what has been promised has been delivered.  Tough? perhaps, but it's a tough old world.The promise is essentially for a text or e-mail contact if they have any ‚Äúsecurity‚Äù concerns BUT no further suspensions.  I have no problems with questions where concern exists.  Security of my account and my money is vital.If they deliver what they have promised they will earn 5 stars.I will certainly give them 5 stars for customer service and their positive reaction.  All organisations make mistakes, what separates the good ones from the bad ones is how they handle and rectify the errors and how they avoid them in the future.The reaction and handling was first class after a faltering start, future avoidance of problems lies still in the future.I do know from experience that your average UK Bank would  not have cared a jot.  So full marks to Monese for the recovery.Original Post Most of the experience is positive BUTI transferred some Sterling into the Sterling account which was then suspended denying me access to my money.  This action breaches Article 1 of the Human Rights ACT 1998.They then demanded information from me without telling me why they had taken the action.They eventually Unblocked the account but still refused to give me any explanation for their action.  "Security" was all they said but would not and will not explain what the "security" issue was.I am now left in the unnacceptable position of not knowing what triggered their action and thus how to avoid it in the future.It's like a game of Russian Roulette albeit not quite so fatal.It not acceptable.

The next day I got an email asking me about my occupation , salary, purpose of monese account , remitter of funds . I sent screen shot of my business account statement where I sent the money from. Also my name and business name on the bank document showing the account was mine. All these was happening before Xmas and I didn't hear from monese until 27th dec. Now I'm on holiday and still cant use my card and they are asking me to send my HMRC SA assessment document. I will be sending them the document when I return and will definitely be closing the account.

We sent also emails , and they have replied that we should wait ,  and do not contact them in next 10 working days. They dont want  just let us withdraw our wages so we have money for food and pay our bills. We dont have money for anything , we have 3years old child to feed, we are alone in UK and we dont have to where from borrow money. We are in contact with sun reporter so hopefully they will describe their shadt techniques of  banking.UPDATE:After a week , and christmas without money, they replied, Im quoting "At Monese, we check various aspects and look to be able to verify your identity in line with government issued requirements. In your situation we haven‚Äôt been able to reach a satisfactory level of confidence and therefore we cannot continue our business relationship". How its possible when they didnt ask for any IDs after verificatiin through canera 14months ago. My three friends already applied for normal high street bank accounts and ditched monese accs after ive told them what happened.

name: Chiddy Brendan
title: Very very terrible experience
content: Very very terrible experience I opened my Monese account about a year ago and was enjoying it a lot. However I stopped using the account about 3 months ago and left it dormant, instead using my main bank account.However, I had already put the account down for my salary at my new job with my university starting October. My salary came in on 22nd November and I couldn‚Äôt access my bank app. I was informed that my account has been blocked and that I‚Äôd receive an email shortly telling me what to do.I never received the email. I called customer care. By this time I had already missed a loan payment on my main bank account. I sent snapshots. Well, the guys over the phone couldn‚Äôt care less. I was sent an email shortly saying I‚Äôd be contacted within three to five working days. They apologized for my missed payments but couldn‚Äôt do anything about it as ‚Äòthe department that handles blocked accounts is different ‚Äò. Fast forward over five working days and I haven‚Äôt been contacted. My rent is due on 1st November and God only knows how much more damage will be done to my already poor credit rating, not to talk of the very embarrassing situation I‚Äôd potentially be in with my landlord.I‚Äôm writing this as an appeal to the guys over at Monese, please sort this issue out for me I beg you. I‚Äôm already switching  my salary account and you‚Äôll never see me again, but please reopen my account so I can access my hard-earned wage.For anyone else considering this bank, I‚Äôve written all the truth I know here, please think twice before you do.Thanks Brendan

name: Edward Greaves
title: Liking it so far...
content: Liking it so far...... But not sure it does everything I was expecting it to.Pros: Option to have a Euro account outside the eurozone and to go for a multi-currency account. Excellent for travel.Really quick set-up (even slicker than with Revolut).Excellent app with user-friendly interface.Card management in-app is a real asset. Can't find your card? Just lock it until you've found it. Traditional banks really need to catch up on this.The USP - this is now a current account that links with the Avios programme and enables you to manage that account all in the same app - collect air miles with your day-to-day banking!And of course - very good exchange rates!Decent variety in services offered: account option is reasonable. Paid account options worth considering if you're likely to use the perks. Easy to change between these schemes in-app as well. Suggested improvements:No link with Paypal - pity aswould enhance P2P offering.Can't find any info on virtual cards - are these available? Savings accounts, interest and the like.Worth checking out. So quick to set up it's worth a go. And for doing so, make sure you earn yourself a fiver by using my code: EDWAR476. Happy travels!

In den AGB werden nach Gusto Verwendungszwecke festgelegt, die bei Monese nicht erlaubt sind. Z.b. SB-Tankstellen, von denen es in Frankreich fast nur gibt, sind alle blockiert, sa√üen bei unserer Bullitour erstmal auf dem Trockenen, vielen Dank. Auch alle bis auf eine einzige Plattform f√ºr Kryptow√§hrungen sind blockiert. Was bildet ihr euch eigentlich ein mir zu diktieren, wo ich mein Geld ausgebe?2. Wieso kann ich auf Android eine empfangen Zahlung nicht stornieren? Support sagt, auf dem iPhone gibt es einen extra button daf√ºr, der bei mir jedoch nicht existiert.4. Wenn ihr mehr verdient als ein Student, bereitet euch vor Papierkram einreichen zu m√ºssen wie ein Krimineller, der sein Einkommen belegen muss. Kommt nicht mit irgendwelchen Gesetzen, bei Sparkasse und Volksbank muss ich das nicht tun und um von denen wegzukommen bin ich urspr√ºnglich zu monese gewechselt.5. Das Abhebelimit ist ein Witz.6. Rumzicken bei manchen Abbuchungen von Onlinek√§ufen, die grundlos storniert werden. Tipp: Einfach mit Paypal bezahlen und dort die Kreditkarte hinterlegen, dann geht es immer durch. Plus: 1.Die App ist √ºbersichtlich und gut handhabbar, die Kategorisierung der ausgaben ist sehr gut. 2. Der Graph oben in der App mit dem Guthabenverlauf ist ein wirklich sehr gutes feature!3. Wenn man nicht oft Bargeld ben√∂tigt, ist es sehr preiswert. In Deutschland nat√ºrlich nur eingeschr√§nkt n√ºtzlich damit, au√üer das geringe Abhebelimit reicht einem nat√ºrlich √ºber den Monat.4. Der Support ist sehr gut, allerdings nicht immer auf deutsch/unter einer deutschen Nummer erreichbar, macht euch auf Auslandsgeb√ºhren gefasst.Fazit: Wenn ihr noch Sch√ºler oder Studenten seid ist Monese wirklich sehr zu empfehlen, f√ºr kleinere Betr√§ge echt unschlagbar. title: You'll be better off elsewhere
content: No doubt I'll get one of these "we only block accounts in the most extreme circumstances to comply with the regulation" but still.Was using Monese to accept payments for my professional IT services for a while, 4-5 months maybe. A few month ago they've requested some source of funds proof and occupation details which I've sent in and it was okay for a while. Then a few months later and after a new payment received from a new client they've requested the same thing once again, for both payment from both clients. Sent everything requested in (I warned them that the invoices I send are rather basic and there's nothing to look at) and in a few days got a wonderful "Notification of account closure: At Monese, we check various aspects and look to be able to verify your identity in line with government issued requirements. In your situation we haven‚Äôt been able to reach a satisfactory level of confidence and therefore we cannot continue our business relationship."Sounds like a template BS which explains nothing. "You can get another account elsewhere" is what CS suggested.TL;DR: if you want to get a decent account for your professional pay I'd suggest looking elsewhere. Thank god my balance was zero!

name: customer
title: Quick to take your money incredibly slow to help their customers.
content: Tried to make a payment at the post office and my card declined when I had more than enough funds in the account. I am leaving for vacation in two days and needed to exchange some money ay the post office with no luck. I then tried to chat through for some help spoke to a robot who had no clue then when I rang there was an estimated hold time of 2 minutes, however, I was on hold for 30 minutes. Great bank if you require a quick bank account in UK but when you actually need help they are useless.
reply: Hi there,We're sad to hear about your negative experience. This is not by any means reflective of our standards of service and customer satisfaction. Upon checking your account we found out that debit card transaction was indeed declined twice at currency conversion shop which has been blocked by our card issuer for security reasons, due to high-risk appetite. Do you know Monese cards can be used anywhere in the world where Mastercard is accepted, and offer exceptionally good FX rates? probably a good idea to use your card on vacation instead of carrying a cash and paying a horrendous amount of fee during conversion.Happy to say our support team proactively called you after reading a review and explained everything in detail, gave possible alternate solutions. We hope that has helped to clear any confusion. Please do contact us if you need any further help.PS: We must also clarify that our phone line system does not let any caller wait for 30 minutes(as you mentioned) under any circumstances. Instead, every caller is promoted to receive a callback upon requesting with IVR by pressing a number 2. Best Regards,The Monese Team

title: Monese Bank is NOT to be TRUSTED as a‚Ä¶
content: Monese Bank is NOT to be TRUSTED as a Financial institution, let alone even a private company.This so called Bank lacks vital communication, very pathetic when it comes to customer service and most of all merely handling simple customer issues.In my case, this Bank apparently returned ¬£8,015 of my money back to source on the 11th of October as I was told, and notified it would take 5 working days to get back to the sender. Meanwhile, as I waited in desperate need of my money due to family commitment and continuous need of my money to work and most importantly care of my 7months old Son. After a week, of constant check with Monese Bank if they had really sent the payment as it has not been received by the company that paid me, I decided to ask for Proof of Payment on the 17th of October, only to be ignored till the next day as usual and then told they ONLY JUST processed the payment the day before, just after I asked for proof of payment they claimed to have made a week before! At this point, I was FURIOUS as this situation has put me in a world of issues, stress and misery. This happening causing me unable to work! And most importantly take care of my Son in every way required. Having to borrow money from friends for food and his daily upkeep! I notified the so called supervisor I will be bringing a suit against the bank as they have no idea what they have done to me! And they will pay! Now on the 18th of October, I requested for the proof of this SECOND claim of payment they told me they made, yet again, they Ignored me for days as the Supervisor called 'Daniel' didn't get back to me at all. I called and emailed them every single day, but no response, leaving me to believe they actually haven't made the payment. After chasing and bombarding them with requests, 5 days later, Monese Bank responded with the Swift reference. Now claiming they made the payment on the 17th. NOT the 11th as they originally claimed, but the 17th as they claimed the second time! 7 days later, still NO MONEY received!!! The reference I was given seems Invalid as stated by the receiving company that sent the money Initially! Been trying to get a hold of someone at Monese for the past day now, no luck at all!Is this what we now call a Bank/Financial Institution!?Is this the type of people you want holding/looking after your money!? Can you TRUST a company that operates like this!? Not me!

name: Gerard
title: Payment blocked by Monese..
content: I've been banking with Monese for approx 9 months now and didn't run into many issues. Unfortunately I recently experienced trouble with one of my (international) transactions. According their email the payment was held by Monese as they wanted to do some security checks. As you can imagine I was very unpleasantly surprised by this and at first I even thought the email wasn't coming from Monese at all (don't get me wrong, but why should a bank email me when they have a secured messaging system in their app?) so I grabbed the phone and called their customer service centre (Yes, they where open on a bank holiday Monday!). The customer service agent on the phone didn't speak proper English (he was French) and we quickly had a view misunderstandings resulting in me feeling not being valued as a customer. Needles to say that I got pretty annoyed and after a quick Google search I found out that multiple people experienced the same issues as I had. This made me feel pretty unpleasant and I decided to sent an email to Monese and leave a 1 star review here on TrustPilot.Within the hour I received a phone call from Monese. My first thought was, O no, here we go.. My account will be blocked, all my money is gone. But.. It was actually the opposite! The supervisor himself called (on bank holiday monday, after 17.00 hours!) and explained why Monese temporary held the payment and apologised for the misunderstandings caused by his team members. He told his site of the story and I told him my site of the story (explaining where the payment was coming from, where it went to and why I decided to use Monese as the middle man). The supervisor was very understanding and offered me two solutions which both where acceptable for me (in both cases I would receive my money within a day or so back).Long story short, if Monese holds a transaction and you haven't breached their terms and conditions they are absolutely willing to work out a solution for you and resolve the issue as soon as possible. This also counts for issues regarding their shared IBAN number. Simply drop them a message in the secured chat in the app or give them a call and within the hour they've located your money and put it into your account!

reply: Hi Henry,We would like to extend our sincerest apologies concerning all the issues that you have faced. However, we only close accounts in the most extreme circumstances. You can find more details in our Terms at monese.com/terms - sections 14 and 15. Also, our record suggests you were contacted by our relevant team & were provided with more details.Please do get in touch with our support team if you have any further questions, as we cannot comment on any account specifics on a public platform.Best Regards,The Monese Team

We would like to take this as an opportunity to clarify what exactly happened.After you complained about not receiving the first debit card our customer support supervisor offered to send you a new card via DHL express shipping, that card returned back to us citing reasons that unable to reach the receiver. We once more verified the address and sent another card to your given address by DHL express shipping again, that card has been delivered already as per tracking ID. (Company did not charge anything for sending extra cards or express delivery as a goodwill gesture)During this whole team, our support team tried contacting you on all channels(phone, email, chat) but all requests went unanswered which is why it took a longer to reach the resolution. They do require a one time fee of ¬£ 5, but if you use this code /P9C2JFGH/ when you register in the appyou will get the card basicaly for free. The Monese app has to be instald in your smart phone.Everything else you need to know about the card is best described in the Monese app, hope this was helpfull for you guys and girls.Cheers.

name: Adrisio Antonio
title: Bad Experience!
content: I wanted to make a transfer of GB6000 from my Monese account to my Monzo account. Instead of calling me or sending me an e-mail to discuss about the money, they just blocked my account which it is going for five days. I am calling them and e-mailing them but nothing was decided yet. I need my money to pay bills with urgency but I don't have access to my account anymore as they have blocked my Monese app. I have no control about my money any more. Waiting for many days for their reply. Today is Friday, 13th of July. They blocked my account and all my money is there and I can't even go out with my friends on this weekend as they kept my money for many days. I called them today and after waiting on the line for 15 minutes, they just turned off the call. I would not recommend Monese as a safe place to leave your money. I am really disappointed with this company as their customer service is awful. Very painful experience!
reply: Hi Adrisio,We're really sorry you had to leave us this review. However, we would like to clarify that our payments team contacted you regarding your case proactively on text channels(In-app chat support and emails) but we did not receive any answer for nearly a week which is why your App access was restricted temporarily which was in line with communication sent earlier by our team(Account was never blocked). Apologies for any inconvenience caused because of this.Happy to say that issue was resolved in an hour or so after we received the desired information from your side which was mandatory to process the payment. Unfortunately, we could not gather as much information based on what has been supplied therefore we will close your account with immediate effect. GB60PRTC*******010140 and ¬£4941.36 in account no. 0*******.Unfortunately, the source account from which these funds were paid is unable to receive returned transfers. In order to return the funds, we require you to provide us with the details of another account of which you are the account holder.Please be advised that these checks are compulsory and in line with industry standard as set by the FCA. Been using the app for a couple of months now and it's been excellent. I have only had to contact customer service once and my experience was positive. The app works well, easy to use and you receive instant notifications when you use your bank card. No complaints. Well done Monese.

title: Best when you just arrive in the country and have no other option. You‚Äôll have to pay a bit more, but until you get your finances figured, it‚Äôs your best bet
content: Great to open an account from scratch. Very quick too. But they want to charge for services other banks provide absolutely for free. Apple Pay or debit card top ups cost a %. Also, bank transfers, both sending and receiving take a couple hours whereas Barclays or Monzo are immediate. I ended up paying 5¬£ + 5‚Ç¨ for two debit cards. Yet I encountered NO hidden or unexpected fees though. They are very clear about those. The only advantage Monese has over competitors is the ability to top up from non-EEA cards (such as from Serbia, for example) and it also saves contacts the best from all competitors I‚Äôve seen. Also, you can have an EU Account along a UK one, and can convert currency between them, which is useful, but others have that and for better exchange rates. Revolut has the absolute best exchange rate I‚Äôve seen, but do read reviews as their customer service is poor.But no way I‚Äôm gonna pay 1¬£ for every cash withdrawal even when in the account‚Äôs home country. I have them as a backup, and a backup only.

reply: Hi there.We are sad to hear that things didn't go down as you expected. As per our record, you were taken care with utmost care by our very experienced support agent throughout your journey with Monese. During that, we made every possible effort to ensure we go extra mile facilitating you. It saddens us deeply that you still had to leave such negative review. Here is the break down of events which we believe is important for our readers to understand the complete situation.-Card delay was caused because of the incomplete/incorrect address entered in the App by the customer before ordering the card.-Our support staff proactively contacted and sent you 2nd debit card to Romania free of charge, which you decided not to wait until the expected delivery date and complained. -We sent a 3rd debit card using 'next day express delivery' free of charge again (You were charged for the only first card which we happily reimbursed as a goodwill gesture)-International payment was delayed because sender sent the payment via wrong payment method which isn't in our control, our support team informed you about the possible reasons of the delay and instructed how to deal with such situations (Instructions how to receive payments are clearly mentioned in the App) Lastly, if customer report issues on a public platform with negative reviews with no details, instead of contacting company support team first in that case, business have the right to approach the customer proactively and ask for more details so they can try to resolve the issue. This isn't a threat or manipulating our customer for good reviews as we do not indulge in such practices.For any further details or feedback, we kindly ask you to contact the support team directly we will be very happy to have your opinion.Best Regards,

name: Nigel Hampson
title: BE EXTREMELY CAREFUL WITH CONTACTLESS CARDS!!!
content: Opened an account with Monese. I'd had it less than 2 weeks when i noticed 3 fraudulent transactions had been attempted by a "merchant" in Birmingham.At this point I hadnt used the card for anything other than my normal ATM withdrawl from a reputable branch of Barclays bank in Burnley.Luckily i had no funds in the account so the 3 payments of ¬£48.00 failed.SO.....customer services contacted.....card blocked and destroyed......new card issued.EXACTLY THE SAME ISSUE AGAIN.This time within 3 weeks of getting the new card and it not being used at all, ANYWHERE,  a fraudulent transaction for ¬£1.80 and another of ¬£78.00.Again I was only saved by there being no funds  in the account so the payments fortunately failed. Again transactions were to a source in the Birmingham area.Clearly, somehow, data is being passed on to third parties who are then using it to gain access to YOUR money. Once I can forgive, but twice is more than a coincidence. Today is a Sunday and they are closed, so I have sent a message instructing them to cancel the 2nd card (again).I will also be purchasing a special anti scanning sleeve that the contactless card can live in, inside my wallet. This stops any fraudulent signals scanning the card illegally.24 HOURS LATERSpoke with Daniel from Monese, who was very helpful. Concerns were addressed and with some modifications to the account at their end and also a couple of things at my end im prepared to give them another chance.
reply: Thank you Nigel for raising this issue and for being available to help us sort it out for you.

name: Brian Smart
title: Monese - realtime transactions, accurate reporting
content: None of the legacy bricks and mortar banks ever gave me what I needed.  Most of them didn't seem to like me because their shop assistants couldn't sell me anything.  So I've been working my way through the challenger banks to see what they offered.  They all had fast in-app sign-up.  They all offered contactless debit cards (none of the dinosaur banks thought I was worthy) and they all had real time notifications, zero foreign transactions fees and in app facilities to disable (and re-enable) the card if you lost it etc.The one thing they seemed to forget was statements!  So it was "here we go again" when I tried Monese.  Hallelujah! Right there on the main menu, it said "Statements".  Some of the other challenger banks had put statements in as an afterthought, but they weren't easy to find.  And when you tried to export their CSV files, your financial management software couldn't make head nor tail of them.  So I tested the Monese CSV the first day I had it.  I was delighted!  It imported first time without a hitch.  Well done, Monese. I didn't think file exports and statements were rocket science but maybe they are?  That makes Monese rocket scientists.  I look forward to seeing where they go next.

title: Good, but not the best...
content: I have opened a few of these internet banks, and Monese is pretty good. Transactions are fast, the app is quite well laid out and the customer support is quite responsive.However, Monese charges for a larger range of transactions, compared to some other providers. Furthermore, having two debit cards instead of one (one for Euro, one for Sterling) is awkward. It pretty much feels like the two accounts live in different worlds. Other providers handle the conversion between currencies better, and all on one single debit card.If these are not important for you, Monese can be recommended.

title: Outstanding account perfect experience from application to accessing my first payment ‚Ä¶
content: i never write reviews but credit where credit is due.  it is rare finding any product or service with out flaws.  with Monese there are none.  Ive used pretty much all pre paid accounts in the UK and this outshines all of them.  set up is fast and easy.  no messing about, all done on the app.  my card was not over sold app predicts a realistic 14 days and  i got it in 2.  no need to wait for pin as its all done on the app.  received my first few payments no drama app told me immediately.  i sent my first payment, i even got to email the receiver it was sent.  i could go on but anyone that wants to bank without drama this is the app. i saw a bad review about fees which i did question but when reading i simply chose the right tariff.  outstanding company that have raised the bar in pre paid accounts.  id say raised the bar in bank accounts full stop thanks for a wonderful service.

From the comfort of my home. MONESE has changed my life and I am so grateful. I look forward to seeing how it grows and what the future holds.

You have to be aware that ATM withdrawals cost ¬£1 each, but otherwise the lack of fees and charges compared to high-street banks is great.However, Monese is authorised by the FCA as a small electronic money provider - it's not a bank, it's more like a tiny Paypal, however, they do claim that you'll get all of your money back if they go bankrupt.The app itself is quick and snappy, and it's only 20MB download, compared to other similar ones. The downsides so far: No web version, so you have to have a phone. Hey, if you sign up using the code SPMJ8D4U, you'll get ‚Ç¨5 when you start sing it, and help me to write in-depth reviews!

name: Dylan Mcallister
title: AVOID! Don't Listen to the positive reviews, this is why you should AVOID!
content: If you want an honest review about Monese based on personal experiences of their service, then please look at this, it will save you so much trouble in the long run, if you ever run into an issue, and no doubt you will at some point. If you ever run into a problem with Monese, then you are never ever ever going to get your money back from them, no matter whether this is 20p or ¬£20,000 you don't have a chance. I withdrew ¬£80.00 from a cash machine, and only actually received ¬£60.00 (I know this is not directly the fault of Monese). However I was told that this issue would be investigated and would take UP TO 45 days, it's now the 52nd day, and despite me chasing almost daily, I've been called a liar and told that the cash machine dispensed the correct amount, it did not. I've asked for regulations to be sent surrounding this, and no one has bothered to respond.Be very wary of what Monese claims to offer, I've had bad experiences with pretty much every aspect of their offerings. - Monese claims that it offers faster payments, it does not, in all instances of me sending a payment it has taken longer than 2 hours, and in one case 48 hours (It was not a bank holiday or a weekend). - Monese claims that it offers Direct Debits, whilst it does it is not able to accommodate them all (As advised by someone from Monese Support). I have been trying for weeks to set up a Direct Debit, which fails each time, meanwhile, that's putting my account into a default. - Monese does not consistently notify you of money going out of in your account, my account is now a negative balance (negative balances are also possible), which no explanation as to why, and no notification, are Monese just helping themselves to my money now? - Monese does not offer BASIC banking protection, it claims to work with the FSCS, I highly doubt it, I would never trust large sums of money to be put into a Monese owned account. It has far wider timescales than your average high street bank for simple things, it's really not worth the hassle. - Things like standing orders are not offered, or correct Direct Debits, these are basic banking features. - The contactless chip is temperamental, and have had contactless payments declined for no reason, you can also use contactless as much as you want, and it never asks you to verify your pin (In my experience), does this seem safe to you?- Monese claim to have a very fast and efficient chat service within their app, they do have a chat service but don't expect a reply immediately, it can sometimes take hours for a response, even days if no one really cares about your query (I've witnessed this a lot). - If you ever need a refund from a pre-authorisation, you need to jump through hoops and need authorisation codes, and confirmation that the money will not be taken from your account, they don't automatically release funds into your account after a few days of them being pending, I've had payment stay pending for weeks and weeks without them being returned to my account (as they should). - Monese charges ¬£4.95 a month for all of the above, save some money and open a basic fee-free bank or post office account to save you the trouble.- They offer online only support, and direct you to this at first point of contact, the service they offer though is slow, inaccurate and never resolves your query. If you ever have an issue with Monese, I urge you to ring and raise a complaint, here's the number: 01706304001, this is freely available to search on google, although is tricky to find. This review is as a result of genuine usage of my Monese account, I'm currently in the process of compiling everything so it can be brought up with the Financial Ombudsman Services. This review, and my complaint is basically over ¬£20.00, you should have never accused me lying in the first place Monese, I hope each and everyone of you take notice of this review. AVOID LIKE THE PLAUGE!!!Note to Monese, As I use your service everyday, I have the right (As confirmed by Trust Pilot) to review my service experience each day, whilst I appreciate this will not alter your score a second time, I will make sure this review is always a most recent one, it is important that people know exactly what type of company you are. If you have any questions, queries or concerns, please direct yourself to the open complaint on my account. AVOID, AVOID, AVOID, AVOID!!!

name: Chris Howlett
title: Beginners guide to Monese
content: If, like me, you have managed to screw your finances so dramatically that nobody wants to give you even the simplest of "proper" bank accounts, this is very likely the most useful app you will ever find for your smartphone.I've tried several other "challenger" banking apps as I have discovered they are known, but Monese has been by far the best so far. Opening an account is a little intense to be frank, and, in the UK at least, you DO require photo ID and proof of address despite the claims made in the Monese promotional material. Once you get set up however, it really couldn't be any simpler. An important detail for me is the speed at which payments arrive, and Monese updates twice an hour at 05 and 35. In my experience you can expect to see your funds on the second update after they were sent. Another key detail, most of these banks charge for cash machine withdrawals. Monese gives you five such transactions free of charge each month before adding a 50p fee for any subsequent withdrawals. A nice touch though, if you don't have enough money to cover the fee you will still be given the cash without charge - this might be a bug however it's been really useful for me up to now. The card does claim to allow cash back however in my experience this is not the case and only smaller stores who know me personally will allow me this facility. Finally, an excellent referral scheme gives you the chance to earn a decent bonus if your friends sign up to monese as well. If you could help both yourself and me by using my code 7HXQSEHB you will be gifted ¬£5 completely free when you finish setting up your new account. I hope I have been helpful!

name: Sebastian
title: Decent app, maybe to expensive
content: Positives First:-I had a good experience with the customer service, they reacted quickly and in a friendly way. At first they couldn't offer a solution, but with an update to the app most issues were fixed. -The app is intuitive, easy to use and nice to look at. What bugs me:I signed up to the mailing list before ‚Ç¨ accounts were offered because of the promise of "no hidden charges". Current accounts in Germany are getting more expensive and I like a system where you pay a fixed amount and can then use your account worry-free. - while charges are not hidden, there is a usually small, sometimes substantial charge associated with many services. That's not what I expected. -the and I clicked on promised the first 2000 people access to an account for 3 months free. Within the app it is not exactly clear when I will be charged the 5¬£ fee. Also, when I first visited the website, I think the monthly fee was advertised as 5‚Ç¨, not GBP. - the localisation of the app is far from perfect, different languages creep in. Just keep it English, that's simpler. All in all, the communication needs to be better. What am I paying, when am I paying it and does "no hidden charges" just mean that charges are written in bold lettering as opposed to not existing?I will probably cancel my subscription and close the account once I start paying all those withdrawal charges, depending on real life use. There are other online-only bank accounts that charge the same for transactions but no monthly fee.

name: Anthony
title: Limited Service
content: So the app locks you out I swear I didn‚Äôt enter it wrong anyway had to call support which is only open Monday to Friday office hours. My current bank is 24/7 which given the lock out meant because I wasn‚Äôt able to call in office hours I was locked out and unable to register my card for Nearly a week due to weekend etc. I understand the need for security, and value that but there must be an easier way plus all I need to login is an email link (when account not locked) not very secure at all. When calling support I waited over 5 minutes and reached a knowledgable yet unenthusiastic support team member. We managed to unlock the account quickly. My current bank has always been quick and even offers an automated service should the line be busy not great but least it‚Äôs there if you want it. Most high street banks offer these services I highlight and also do most of the other app/internet only banks. There is a monthly cost after trial which again is something to consider given the limited service and support. I can‚Äôt recommend over my current high street bank or other app only banks. I can get more for less so unless you send A LOT of money aboard it‚Äôs reallly not worth the service you get and I certainly would switch to it as my main account.My story might not be a common one least I hope not, but does highlight the limits of the service.
reply: Hi Anthony,Thanks a million for your review.  We always welcome feedback about how to make ours service better.  We can definitely make the lock-out process easier to resolve and hope to have a new process launched for this very shortly (this isn't an overnight process due to the need for ensuring security at all times).Our support can be busy at certain times of the week (Monday morning and Friday's in particular), but generally you should have to wait much less than 5 minutes - although we appreciate that is not the impression we gave with your wait on this occasion.  Our phone support is currently office hours, but we run in-app chat support until 22:00 every day should you need any help.  We are one of the few new banking services to offer comprehensive phone support and are working hard to improve this all the time.There is also a lot of work done in the background to ensure security with your mobile device, so although we make the process feel easy with email registration, there is a lot more we are doing that goes unseen to ensure your security.We do understand that for many people, you can get an account from a traditional high street bank under a 'free whilst in credit model', but the fees in that case are often hidden (such as charges for a refused Direct Debit where there is no charge from us) and turn up as a surprise.  We prefer that charges are up front and something that can be relied upon.As always, we highly appreciate your feedback about how we make our service better and would love to chat if you have any other feedback.  Just drop us a line to support@monese.com and we will call you back.The Monese Team

I have now requested a funds transfer and true to form, the high street issuer is dragging its feet.The days of the Big Four are numbered if this is the future of banking and it can't come soon enough for this satisfied customer. Download with confidence and experience what you've been missing and deserved for so long.

name: Juliana Mattar
title: Support needs adjusting asap
content: Opening the bank account was very easy and staff were friendly and helpful and during the first days I got complete and timely answers from chat support. Topping up my account from another UK account was also easy and the money was credited in the same day (although it took approx. 4 hours). However, I had to bring money to the UK and my monese account by means of an international foreign exchange transaction and something went wrong. Neither the bank of origin nor Monese can tell me what happened and staff and support from Monese are neither helpful nor timely. Often I send messages or emails in the morning and do not hear from Monese for over 1 day. It has been almost 4 days now that I do not have an answer or a solution to my problem nor have I had decent support from Monese in this regard. Considering my urgency and the sums involved, I suggest Monese come up with a telephone support service for emergencial cases. As such I am having to appeal to a third party (trustpilot) to put some pressure on Monese to provide adequate support.Edit - Monese representatives contacted me and were so very helpful! They understood the problem and my urgency and helped me fix it in a timely manner. Really, after they provided me with a telephone number and point person to deal with my issue, everything ran very smoothly and they went to great lengths to make sure I found my money and was able to make all payments on time. Great banking and customer services! Truly recommend, especially for expats living in London.
reply: Glad that we were able to sort things for you.  Please let us know if there is anything else we can do to help.Warmest regardsThe Monese Team
