name: Nuno Gil
title: I have waited for a long time on ‚Ä¶
content: I have waited for a long time on pipeline for a beta EUR account after so much advertising and reading positive comments on the Internet, so I decided to give you a try. I was excited when I received an email saying I already could register my EUR account, which I did, verified it, ordered card and made the first deposit. Then the nightmare began, I've transferred a small amount from my current account to Monese in order to test and verify it worked properly before moving more funds. It was a SEPA transfer that usually takes 1 business day and it was lost for a week without any help from the support telling me it can take more time, that they were going to ask their payment processor partner. Finally after 1 week the payment was returned to my current account to which Monese support replied they didn't know what happened, acknowledged that everything was done properly and IBAN, BIC were right at the transfer. Then support told me they were going to investigate and ask their partner what happened so the payment was returned and that was a few days ago. How can anyone rely in a "banking" that relies on 3rd party suppliers and payment processing partners that don't give answers about our money? Terrible, terrible experience. I've got a card, an account but no answers and no way to deposit money. I've even tried do transfer from another account and when I put IBAN they say they can't retrieve BIC automatically because destination bank didn't updated it globally. I could bring many people to use your current accounts but now I won't, not until I see any changes and a resolution. I was told that you've asked your partner for more details on september 1st.

name: M
title: Can't rely on them.
content: Pros: Great UI, quick customer service, easy setup for immigrants to the UK.Cons: They recently upgraded accounts to Current Accounts, but failed to mention that the new cards do not work for most online payments, and there is now a severe delay (3-4 days) for incoming payments, eg. payslips. I was led to believe I could rely on Monese as a proper challenger bank, but turns out they're just an interim solution. Will be switching away shortly.
reply: Hi MThanks so much for leaving a review and letting us know your thoughts.  We'd love to know about the particular issues you have experienced so that we can tackle them for you.  Just to let you know,  all our incoming payments are processed every 2 hours, and from Monday PM will be processed every 30 minutes.  We are not in control of when these are sent, but if there has been a delay with a specific payment, we would be happy to look into it for you.  Likewise, with online payments, we are aware of a couple of minor issues with the new card with acceptance by EE (which we and Mastercard are tackling with them), but if you are aware of others that we can tackle for you, then we will jump straight on it.  We would love to keep you as a customer, so please do get in touch with our team (mentioning this review) and we will get to it.The Monese team

name: Tirath Singh
title: Take FULL control of your money!
content: After getting fed up with almost every traditional high street bank, I finally signed up to test few challenger banks operating in the UK market, Monese being one of the key players amongst them. Here's my experience so far:"I downloaded the app, applied via in-app application system however I was not instantly approved and apparently they had to process it manually and it took additional 3-5 working days but finally it was opened. I am really enjoying the app layout, design and user experience. I really don't mind paying 4.95 GBP per month especially when you're offering add-ons such as Direct Debits, Faster Payments, EUR account with additional debit card etc. Contactless card works nicely and I've had no trouble so far!"Things I would like to see more of/Not Impressed with so far! - "Apple Pay(and Samsung/Android Pay etc.) is one thing people would love to have since many customers are buying wearables now a days. Secondly, Faster Payment is not really FAST compared to UK high street banks (with my Natwest and HSBC it gets credited within seconds even though disclaimer says within 2 hours!) however in case of Monese it takes anything between 1-2 hours as minimum! This needs to be fixed to make it work much more quicker (Not a big issue but sometimes we need money a lot quicker!) and Lastly, UK based IBAN number can be beneficial to those receiving salary in GBP pounds. Some employers (including mine) cannot except non GB IBAN numbers.That being said, I am aware Monese is constantly evolving and innovating so I can surely expect lots of improvements/new features over the coming days, months and years :)Everything else is PERFECT and I would highly recommend this product to :- Expats/Immigrants- Frequent Eurozone Travellers- Tech Savvy People- People who can't be bothered to visit branches for lots of things e..g statements, direct debits, payments etc.
reply: Thanks for such a comprehensive review Tirath.  That's really valuable feedback.  Apple/Android pay are both coming (in the works now) - Android Pay is likely to be slightly faster to market than Apple Pay (more down to respective processes at the other end than our side).  On Faster Payments, all out-going payments are made at a maximum of 30 minutes.  Incoming has been slightly slower until now, but will be moving to every 30mins early next week (after final testing this week).  We are also working on real-time faster payments and expect to have these implemented around the end of the year.   You can of course make instant faster payments to any other Monese user anywhere in Europe (whether they have a UK account or a European IBAN account) - although we realise that not everybody is a Monese user yet üòâ.  Let us know if you have any issues paying into our new European IBANs (they are live on the Step2 SEPA platform) as we are following up on every instance where there are issues - we realise there will be a few, even thought we have done extensive testing across Europe.  Localised IBANs are also in the works but will take another few months to be finalised.  Keep in touch and thanks again.The Monese Team

name: Mark Austin
title: I switched to this account to move away ‚Ä¶
content: I switched to this account to move away from traditional profit focused banks. So far been a relatively positive experience. The full account now allows direct debits and the deposit limits are high enough to use this as my main account. I switched from UAccount because of their lower limits.The app works well now, although there were a few bugs initially and the alert functions and balance on-screen all help with budgeting. The only down side I've come across so far is a recent unauthorised withdrawal (2 in fact) which seemed to have slipped any anti-fraud checks. Having phoned to complain a new card was swiftly sent but the amounts will not be credited for at least 45 days! My traditional bank would re-credit such transactions immediately. Aside from this however, very happy
reply: Hi Mark,Let me start by saying we are sorry for the unauthorised transactions. Thank you for calling in and we are happy we resolved the issue. It was a very peculiar incident for anything to slip through our extremely stringent anti-fraud checks and especially due to the very small value of the transactions which is impossible to withdraw from an ATM. We are diligently looking into this and we will keep you updated, Mark.Let us also say thank you so much for the in depth review! We are so happy that you are enjoying everything about Monese, bar the above incident, and the addition of Direct Debits now means that you are using us as your main account! We are so glad to have you on the Monese team and hope that we keeping shipping features that you love!All the best from us at Monese!

name: Rachel clarke
title: Reassured after being given accurate information.
content: Re-rating as a 5 as very happy with the account management and the add on euro card account.***************  Old Review Below  *****************  Reassured after been given accurate information.   Happy to confirm account is fine with minimal stress  Rating as a 4 now as would still prefer a Visa card!***************  Old Review Below  *****************  Not very happy withe account changes.  Direct debits are not need and would prefer to have a Visa card having Mastercard with a different account.  Also noticed you are starting to credit check people "use an ID verification agency or credit reference agency both prior to and following issue of your Monese Account for this purpose and who will add details to your record of our request for a search."How is this  going to work for people who live outside the UK?  And what about people who joined you because they had a bad credit history?
reply: Hi Rachel,We are sorry that you are not a fan of the account upgrade! Direct Debits enable us to be on feature parity with traditional banks and are a necessity for most of our customers so that they can pay bills or rent as Monese is their main and only account. In regards to switching to Mastercard, we felt that we could offer more with them and so switched but we appreciate you would prefer Visa and apologise for that. We do not perform any credit checks on our customers when they onboard to Monese. The only checks we do in some cases are to check a customers address/identity so we can confirm they are who they say they are to remain compliant with regulations and maintain our customer's safety. Anyone can sign up for a Monese account regardless of their nationality or if they live outside of the UK or if they have a good, bad or no credit history. Better yet, very shortly we will be allowing customers to sign up for our Euro accounts which will run simultaneously with our GBP account. You will receive a Euro IBAN and a new card Euro white card - you can sign up for the wait list at www.monese.com/euro. We hope that this clears things up in terms of not needing anything to do with a credit history, Rachel. We appreciate the feedback in regards to you not needing Direct Debits and preferring the Visa card and would love to hear from you if you have any more feedback at feedback@monese.com. All the best from all of us at Monese.

name: Jan Jensen
title: Had a bad experience, but must say Monese made a nice comeback
content: Had a bad experience with their customer support, but must say Monese made a nice comeback, thank for your help and support Max
reply: Hi Jan,We have been trying to get in contact with you and would love to help you through the onboarding process. When you sign up for Monese you need to do so with a national ID card, driving license, or passport. Unfortunately, we cannot accept other forms of identification with simply your name on.The point of starting Monese was to give everyone fair access to a bank account with no exclusions and we stand by that philosophy but we do need to verify who our customers are by asking for the documents I previously mentioned so that we can remain compliant with industry regulations and keep our customers safe. We are tremendously sorry you have had a bad experience with our customer service, we hear great things from our customers about their experiences with our customer service and therefore are shocked by what you have said. We would love to get in contact with you if you could respond to the emails we have sent we can rectify the situation and get back to a place where you are happy to use Monese!Thank you for your feedback and we really hope to hear from you. All the best.

name: customer
title: You pay, You Save
content: They charge you money for what you can get for free. But they do it so that you save in the long run! All so they would want you to believe. As all you need to do is google cash plus and you will get something even better a card that you can do everything with as you would a bank account. That includes direct debits and standing orders!
reply: Hey!Our transparent fee of ¬£4.95 / month gives you access to what most would expect from a current account.One of the reasons we started Monese was to reveal the brutal hidden charges slapped onto customers by the traditional high street UK banks and let our customers save by paying a monthly fee with us instead of throwing away fortunes without even knowing about it. An average Monese customer saves money by paying our monthly fee over having a traditional bank account. We never try to up-sell products such as overdraft protection which can be as much as ¬£8.00 a month alone!Not only that, but to actually give the opportunity for the unbanked, that were turned out the door as they did not have a credit history or UK residential address, the equal right to have a bank account - And we wanted them to have it in minutes!Another huge point for us was that we wanted to create global on-demand banking. We knew customers would want to send money abroad to family or friends and the extortionate charges made by banks for foreign exchange could carry on no longer. That's why we let our customers send money abroad at rates up to 8x cheaper than the traditional UK high street banks so that their friends and family could get what they deserved instead of being fined for it.On top of these international transfers we wanted to let our customers have global usage of their Monese cards at a fraction of the price while letting them access the best possible foreign currency conversion, again saving up to 8x as the typical UK banks you would know well.These are but a few reasons that make us so much more transparent, cheaper and better than a traditional bank. The BEST part is that we are constantly adapting our product to fit our users wishes. We are always bringing in new features to make sure we are giving the best service we can possibly give.We hope that this clears the monthly fee up for you and you can see that even with a monthly fee and if you have any further questions please do send us your queries to feedback@monese.com.From all of us, our kindest regards!

reply: Hey Jeton,Our transparent fee of ¬£4.95 / month gives you access to what most would expect from a current account.One of the reasons we started Monese was to reveal the brutal hidden charges slapped onto customers by the traditional high street UK banks.We created Monese to save our customers the fortunes they were throwing away to banks by the hiding of their fees and charges in day to day transactions. Not only that, but to actually give the opportunity for the unbanked, that were turned out the door as they did not have a credit history or UK residential address, the equal right to have a bank account - And we wanted them to have it in minutes!Another huge point for us was that we wanted to create global on-demand banking. We knew customers would want to send money abroad to family or friends and the extortionate charges made by banks for foreign exchange could carry on no longer. That's why we let our customers send money abroad at rates up to 8x cheaper than the traditional UK high street banks so that their friends and family could get what they deserved instead of being fined for it.On top of these international transfers we wanted to let our customers have global usage of their Monese cards at a fraction of the price while letting them access the best possible foreign currency conversion.I see you have mentioned 3 cash withdrawals monthly, we in fact allow 10 cash withdrawals monthly - Which I'm sure you'll be happy to hear!These are but a few reasons that make us so much more transparent, cheaper and better than a traditional bank. The BEST part is that we are constantly adapting our product to fit our users wishes. We are always bringing in new features to make sure we are giving the best service we can possibly give.We take on board our customers reviews with relish. We very much appreciate when our customers take the time out to tell us how they are feeling about Monese with things they dislike and we can improve. So, we are very grateful for your feedback, Jeton, and I hope that you continue to use Monese!From all of us, our kindest regards!

name: Colin
title: Gaming changing......
content: I am not someone who normally provides reviews on products, or services, but I recently signed up to use Monese and my first experience of using the card over the weekend was fantastic!!  The registration process was quick and user friendly.  It took five minutes and no paper!!  This is far removed from my last experience of setting up a bank account, which took weeks and was a hugely frustrating process.I travel overseas regularly on business and holiday.  The norm for me is to get some foreign currency in cash (to use for taxis etc.) at the departure airport, and then use my credit card, or bank debit card, for larger expenditure (hotels, dinner etc.) when I am in-country.I am normally oblivious to the exchange rate I get on transactions.  However, since signing up to Monese I started to look at what rate I get in different situations.  At the airport I noticed the Sterling / Euro rate I would have got was parity!  The actual rate as ¬£1:‚Ç¨1.1588.  I have been throwing money away for years.I used the Monese card over the weekend in a number of places and saved money.  I saved ¬£25 over 4 days through a combination of lower transaction costs and better exchange rate (Monese gives you the wholesale exchange rate).  Over the course of a year Monese is going to save me hundreds of pounds.  This is money that previously I was throwing away without thought.  Monese provides a genuine value service and is simple to use.  I urge all foreign travellers to sign up!

name: Robin Young
title: Green Eyed Greed Got Me!
content: I pride myself on always getting a good deal so when I went skiing last month I pre booked some foreign currency at my local post office and got ‚Ç¨550 for ¬£500, a rate of 1.1. Much better than the exchange rate at the airport which is rubbish (one euro to ¬£1). I was chuffed because I'd gained an extra ‚Ç¨50 which I figured would pay for a nice free boozy lunch on the slopes!It ended up being a very boozy and expensive long weekend and I ran out of cash! I was going to use my credit card but one of the lads said it'd cost me a packet with their foreign currency exchange fees. He had a Monese card which I'd never heard of before and claimed he was getting spot rate with no fees! Frankly I didn't really believe him so challenged him to prove it and he showed me the bill. He was getting 1.17!I was gutted! I realised I'd chucked away an extra ‚Ç¨35! The upside was we came to a gentleman's arrangement where he paid my share and I paid him in sterling back in the uk. I couldn't bear the thought that he would be getting ‚Ç¨70 more than me in the future for every grand's worth of holiday expenses so I signed up for a card as soon as I got home and have to say it was very quick and does everything it says on the tin.I still don't understand why they give you such a good deal compared to the other banks but hey I'm not complaining! Great product, wish I'd thought of it!

name: kimberly
title: A real revelation to me!
content: I have a home abroad and the opportunity to send money over and withdraw money virtually at spot is incredible. It was always a pain trying to find the best rate, and monese has really solved a genuine headache for me! I have recommended it to loads of people as opening an account is always a difficult process, I have been a client of Lloyds for over 30 years and have two business accounts, and it still took 9 weeks to open up a third business account!!!

name: Arthur Walsh
title: Dangerously good
content: One of the simplest set up processes had me instantly hooked on Monese, but the best was yet to come once I found out how easy it was to use the app to make international transfers, and at spot rate as well! It's made spending money when travelling so much less of a hassle, thoroughly recommend to anyone thinking of joining, Monese certainly are putting the ease back in money.

name: Jack Opperman
title: Love it
content: Exactly what my friend said it would be I got everything I would expect from a bank and only took me a few minutes to set up the account

name: Charlie Rennocks
title: Too easy to use!!
content: Excellent service that has helped me massively!

name: Edward Stokes
title: Perfect for a traveller
content: I have never been happier stumbling upon Monese. For someone who travels a lot and has ALWAYS been stung by huge bank fees, Monese has saved me a fortune. I feel so secure knowing that anywhere I go I will never be hit by hidden charges from my bank and I can immediately track exactly the spot exchange rate I get abroad.

name: Joe Dipre
title: fantastic
content: Easy to set up, convenient to use and have saved a ton of money by using this!

name: Paul Sadler
title: Amazing
content: Exactly what I needed - I send money back to my mum in France and I now use my Monese account for every transfer! I get the best rates and I'm saving fortunes to what I was paying with my Natwest account. Thank you guys !!

name: Nick O'Keeffe
title: Really simple and quick to use.
content: For someone who isn't tech savvy this is a really fast and easy program to use and I will definitely be using it again.

name: Jamie Pitt
title: Super fast and great international transfers
content: Set my account up because of a recommendation from a friend, I'm so happy he told me to. Set it up in under 5 minutes and could start sending money abroad at nearly spot rate. Saved a fortune - thank you Monese!

name: Amy Olivia Crawford
title: Everything you'd expect from a bank
content: A friend recommended this to me and I couldn't believe how easy and quick it was to make an account. Love the product!

name: Matt Desmond Kealey
title: Fantastic service
content: Extremely fast to set up and very happy with live tracking of my spending through notifications, which is a great feature.

name: Charlie Smith
title: Fastest account I've ever made!
content: I made the account in literally a few minutes and I could send receiving money immediately!

name: Matt Swabey
title: Overalls a great way to bank especially for someone that travels!
content: Only a 0.5% fee when used abroad and no ATM charges, which I enjoy particularly as I travel a lot as a part of my work. It was also very quick and efficient to set up as don't have to provide credit history etc!

name: Jamie Ray
title: Changing the banking game
content: Quick and easy to set up, and great for tracking my spending. Also regularly transfer money abroad as part of my job and save a ton by avoiding extortionate fees!
reply: Hi Jamie,Many thanks - it's great to have you onboard!We are really happy you are using the international payments feature straight from your Monese balance, we wanted to make sure we could give our customers the best possible exchange rates and be transparent with our fees.We hope you carry on saving with us :)

name: Reuben Slater
title: Excellent
content: Great service - banks need to take notice
reply: Hi Reuben,Cheers for leaving a review!I am sure they are already taking notice ;)We love hearing from our customers when they love the service we provide, thanks again, Reuben!

name: Will Greenhalgh
title: Brilliant App & Service
content: Great service with a really user friendly app.
reply: Hi Will,Great news! We try to make sure our app is the best it can be and it's great to hear that we are providing that for you :D

name: Ieuan Owen
title: Saved me money!
content: I used my monese account abroad to avoid the hideous fees charged by the big banks.Monese offer a transparent spot rate and flat fee, so you can avoid the big charges. I offered to pay for lunch for 8 when skiing and saved almost ¬£10 on what my main UK bank would have charged.Not many people have heard of monese but I'd recommend them as they have a very transparent and low cost offering.
reply: Hi Ieuan,Thank you for taking the time to leave a review. We make sure that everything we charge is transparent and to ensure our customers get the best possible exchange rates you can get when abroad.It makes us so happy knowing we can help save you money and will continue to do so!

name: Jordan rothman
title: Quick, simple, effective and excellent value for money
content: Monese came recommended by a friend and I was originally sceptical - I don't like fuss and signing up for new things. Monese eliminates all the fuss by making the process easy and by ensuring that your time is well spent. The card gives me access to better rates than I would get with my bank and I've recommended it on to others!
reply: Hi Jordan,We don't like the fuss of taking weeks to sign up for a bank account either, that's why we made Monese!Thanks a lot for recommending us, we hope to help everyone get a no-fuss Monese account and keep providing the best possible rates ;)

name: Char Stott
title: Fantastic!
content: Love it - it has saved me money and the customer service is great! Thanks Monese :)
reply: Amazing!We are so happy you love Monese, welcome aboard Char.

name: Ben Teicht
title: Top Notch
content: Smashing Company
reply: Thanks, Ben!We hope to keep smashing it for you :D

name: Cameron Scott
title: They freeze everyone's money...
content: Beware, I am a British citizen. I took a Monese account as a secondary bank, and I liked the idea of the whole "app only" set up. I confirmed my ID with a passport, driving licence and also had proof of address.I barely used the card, I left ¬£2,000 on it which came from my RBS bank account, for 3 months. The first transaction I made was to pay a BT bill, instantly my account was frozen. I then received an email stating "due to AML we are closing your account, your funds will be returned to the bank within 60 days".How many peoples money do they hold for up to 60 days? I feel like this is a little troubling? Do the maths. When people have proved who they are, have confirmed ID and have no went out with the terms and conditions? I work in financial services myself, I understand KYC and AML regulations, I never breached any of these and MONESE have no appeal process to ask why they have closed your account or frozen it. I just do not recommend trusting this company with your money, escpially if you needing access to the money you hold on this account daily. It is a terrible solution for Day to day banking.Be warned, be aware and only use Monese if entirely necessary. I think more will come to light about their true motives in the future.

name: Roo Aubeeluck
title: Simple Banking at its best.
content: Opened my account on the train and received my card within a few days. This was my first experience with a banking app and I was very impressed to say the least. I still cant get enough of how easy the transfers are, I have a Santander mobile banking app and its the worst to use, have to register the person then send the money. On Monese, its a straight away transfer. Have used the card all over the place and had no issues. Also like to track to expenses, makes saving much easier. Thanks Monese

name: Chris
title: Easy, Simple Banking
content: Opened account on mobile phone and received my card within 3 days. Uploaded more documents and was full verifed member within 5 days or opening account.I was dubious at first and sent a small amount from my TSB account to see what happened, took a while to come through but this is becauase they use a 3rd party faster payment system at present so is only processed every few hours and not at weekends. Phoned up to confirm the verification and answered straight away, have also used their inbuilt chat/support system which I got responce from very promptly. Have used the card all over the place and had no issues. I like the instant notification wtih balance and transactions.

name: Ian
title: Absolute Crap
content: Sent a direct messgge to them, still no reply 7 hours later. Most certainly will not be using any of their services. Cannot trust them to respond if any problems arise.Total waste of space.
reply: Hey Ian,We are sorry that you had to wait so long for a reply. Our direct message service runs on Monday to Friday, 9-5 GMT. If you messaged us out of these hours then the wait time would be substantially longer. When are customer support are not overloaded we aim to reply in around 30 minutes to any queries. Thank you very much for your feedback it is very helpful to hear from our customers what they aren't happy with. We are constantly trying to improve the product and provide the best service we can so we do really appreciate you taking the time out to write a review for us.Could you email us at feedback@monese.com and provide your name so we can locate what the issue was you were having initially so we can make sure to help you where we can. Thank you again, Ian.

name: Samuel Vincent Paal
title: Awesome service and customer support
content: Registration took only 3 minutes :) App is really easy to use.

name: Octopus
title: Easy & Convenient
content: Does what it says on the tin. Easy to set up an account, upgrade and and use. Loads of services included in the monthly fee! Great value if you use the account a lot. Nice card too and works everywhere. Can't wait for direct debits, which Monese is saying will be available in the future.

name: Nordica
title: Best UK bank account
content: Very convenient when you're new to the UK. No need to queue, simple onboarding process and you already have a bank account in your mobile app within some minutes!

name: Joe Allison
title: Very impressed with Monese
content: It was so fast and easy to open an account with Monese. Their app is so much better than any of the other banking apps I've had in the past. Excellent customer service also, I would recommend to anyone in need of a bank account.

name: Sander Sedrik
title: Amazing experience
content: Compared to other platforms on the market Monese has made a truly remarkable mark. The easy-to-use interface and good customer service  are on a higher level than others. In my opinion, the BEST choice.

name: Maarja
title: Convenient and fast
content: Easy to use. Everything you need to do available from Monese App.

name: Fayder Florez
title: Monese current account
content: No doubts, the best current account app in the market. Keep up the good work!

name: Donna Care
title: SO EASY TO OPEN AN ACCOUNT!!!!
content: After years of being in and out of the UK without a real bank account, I found MONESE and now I can pay my rent from a local bank account :)

name: Fiona Voolaine
title: Best banking solution I have used so far.
content: Best banking solution I have used so far. Love the offline balance feature!

name: Pavel Yakov
title: Excellent service
content: Great customer support too. I will recommend Monese anyday.

name: Henry
title: Account opened quickly
content: took me only few minutes to get Monese bank account, have been struggling with Barclays for ages. Why are other banks so slow!

name: Ragnar M
title: Great new bank!
content: While some of us have enjoyed mobile banking for more than a decade, this has not been the case in the UK and when I heard about Monese, I decided to give it a try. Everything from the account opening to your statements is digital and really smooth. My card arriving in little more than a week and I've been really impressed how easily everything works!

name: Lauri Haav
title: Opened a bank account during a taxi ride
content: I literally downloaded the app, made a picture of my ID card, took a selfie, registered my address and got the bank account opened during a short taxi ride. That was pretty amazing even for a resident of a country (Estonia) were general elections are held on-line!I'm not a UK resident so the VISA card took about a week to arrive by post for free, which was fast enough for me. Sending money from my euro bank account to Monese UK account required some extra information which I failed to add so the customer support contacted me in order to finish the transaction.

name: M. Daniel
title: An awesome alternative to traditional banks
content: Monese is a fantastic solution for anyone that has recently arrived in the UK and needs a bank account to receive a UK salary. It's just like a regular bank, you can make payments using the app, receive pay / salary, send money abroad cheaply (pretty great at 0.5% on top of the real rate) and just generally manage your money from anywhere. I use it as my main bank account daily and have had no issues!.

name: Lemming
title: Monese is not what it says on the tin!
content: I have been using Monese almost from the outset (more than 8 month by now), as I love to support start-ups and disruptive businesses, but there comes a time when one must expect even start-ups to be working fully and to deliver a quality service ‚Äì unfortunately this is not the case with Monese.At the beginning, I was willing to ignore teething issues, but these seem to be continuing and even get worse as time goes by.Over time I have experienced issues with limits relating to cash withdrawals, both in UK and in Germany, I have found out that I cannot make bank transfers to 3‚Äôd party countries, I cannot move funds from my PayPal account to my Monese account, their support takes up to 3 weeks to answer even messages marked URGENT, their support is only available between 08:00 and 17:00 UK time and only Monday to Friday, you can maximum have ¬£ 40,000 in your account at any given time ‚Äì and I can go on.On top of this, they have now started charging ¬£ 5.00 per month for the account, an account which turns out to basically be a pre-paid VISA card!Truth be told, I do like the philosophy that they sell, being a UK bank account for everyone living in EU where they offer standard current account features, but I am afraid that I feel they not even live up to that!Monese, I am sorry, but I will now start to look for alternatives to you ‚Äì you have disappointed me dramatically by "selling" a product which I feel you have not delivered!

name: lee chadwick
title: great bank low fees
content: Monese is a new banking app that you can send fast money transfers from your mobile app so easy you can see what you spend what monies go in your account with real time up to the minute spends and regular updates, you get a contactless visa which is so easy nowadays, all your banking is done on your app and customer service is very helpful, at the moment they don't have the direct debit facilities but it is something their gonna be getting onboard very soon but its just a small fee of ¬£4.95 a month so no charges for money withdrawals, no charge for depositing money or fast tranfers its all in the ¬£4.95 month, the good part I love is you can go to a ''PayPoint'' and deposit money instead of waiting in banks

title: App blocked
content: Hello,I have installed the app and sent my identity document's pictures, but I can not pass the verification step,when it asks to say a number loudly and to position my head in the oval shape. In fact, after saying the numbers loudly and correctly position my head, it asks to look right or left then back. At this step, the app gets blocked!!Please help!Regards

title: good
content: i am pleased,it is a good thing.
reply: Hello there!Thank you very much for your kind review!We're very happy to hear that you're satisfied with our solutions :)All the best,The Monese team

reply: Hi Roman!Thanks a lot for sharing your impressions with us :)We're already looking into adding new languages to the app! Stay tuned for news about it!All the best,The Monese team

Unfortunately, we cannot comment on any account specifics on a public platform.Thanks for your understanding!All the best,The Monese team

name: Vlad
title: AVOID!
content: First of all , no one even read in app chat , in few days they just drop your question . You can call them , but phone support is useless , all they can say is "We will escalate your case , wait for an E-mail ".September 18.2019 I've made a transaction of 56 ¬£ , UK to UK account , It was pending till October 29.2019 . I called them about ten times asking to cancel this transaction because I already paid to person with different account . Instead of resolve the issue they just suspended my account , (with money in it of course) . Send me nonsense questioning , Questions I already replied long time ago ..All those prepaid accounts companies have one excuse "We are FCA regulated company " , I wonder how did they get the license ..I strongly advice you DO NOT keep any money with any FCA regulated prepaid accounts companies . Unless you are ready to lose your money.This company exploiting trustpilot's reporting system to hide unwanted reviews ... draw your conclusions

title: They are a very caring company who‚Ä¶

name: Robert
title: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card‚Ä¶
content: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card issued by Sberbank Croatia and I cannot topup from my MasterCard issued by Sberbank Croatia. With both of them I can topup my revolut account/card.

name: Matteo Ricci
title: Conto bloccato / Blocked account
content: Mi hanno bloccato il conto dopo un anno che lo utilizzo davvero poco. In tutto ci ho fatto girare meno di 500 euro. Uso la carta solo per Pagare il parcheggio della mia auto. Praticamente poco e niente.Oggi mi ritrovo conto bloccato gi√† da diversi giorni. Mi richiedono documentazione sulla provenienza del denaro. Invio i documenti dopo solo 1 ora dalla loro mail di blocco. Ad oggi dopo 6 giorni nessuna risposta, ho scritto nuovamente ma ancora nessuna risposta.Servizio scadente e assurdo. Meno male che lo utilizzavo solo per cose futili e non ci ho fatto affidamento. Rimango dell'idea che REVOLUT tratta meglio i suoi clienti e consiglio a tutti di abbandonare questa inutile e complicata piattaforma. QUi su Monese il cliente non vale nulla, infatti il cliente non riceve mai risposte. Rispondono solo alle recensioni.****They blocked my account after a year that I use very little. In all, I made it run less than 500 euros. I only use the card to pay for parking my car. Virtually nothing and nothing.Today I find myself stuck for several days already. They ask me for documentation on where the money came from.Send the documents after only 1 hour from their block mail. To date, after 6 days no reply, I wrote again but still no answer.Poor and absurd service. Luckily I used it only for trivial things and I didn't rely on it.I remain convinced that REVOLUT treats its customers better and I advise everyone to abandon this useless and complicated platform.Here on Monese the customer is worth nothing, in fact the customer never receives answers. They only respond to reviews.

name: Erison Nascimento
title: Monese doesn't replay my email
content: I sent an email to Monese 3 days ago and I didn't receive any answer, M15173089

name: Birce
title: Horrible customer service
content: Horrible customer service, takes ages to get a response for a request. I guess asking for a debit card is the primary thing you could ever ask from your bank and should not take you weeks until you get it. I have been waiting for a single response for the last 5 days Monese. If replying takes so long, cannot imagine how long will it take me to receive the card, if it ever happens!

name: Andrew Donaldson
title: Taking over a week to process my‚Ä¶
content: Taking over a week to process my application? I don't think so - bye-bye Monese!

Instead of resolve the issue they just suspended my account , (with money in it of course) . Send me nonsense questioning , Questions I already replied long time ago ..All those prepaid accounts companies have one excuse "We are FCA regulated company " , I wonder how did they get the license ..I strongly advice you DO NOT keep any money with any FCA regulated prepaid accounts companies . title: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card‚Ä¶

name: Matteo Ricci
title: Conto bloccato / Blocked account
content: Mi hanno bloccato il conto dopo un anno che lo utilizzo davvero poco. In tutto ci ho fatto girare meno di 500 euro. Uso la carta solo per Pagare il parcheggio della mia auto. Praticamente poco e niente.Oggi mi ritrovo conto bloccato gi√† da diversi giorni. Mi richiedono documentazione sulla provenienza del denaro. Invio i documenti dopo solo 1 ora dalla loro mail di blocco. Ad oggi dopo 6 giorni nessuna risposta, ho scritto nuovamente ma ancora nessuna risposta.Servizio scadente e assurdo. Meno male che lo utilizzavo solo per cose futili e non ci ho fatto affidamento. Rimango dell'idea che REVOLUT tratta meglio i suoi clienti e consiglio a tutti di abbandonare questa inutile e complicata piattaforma. QUi su Monese il cliente non vale nulla, infatti il cliente non riceve mai risposte. Rispondono solo alle recensioni.****They blocked my account after a year that I use very little. In all, I made it run less than 500 euros. I only use the card to pay for parking my car. Virtually nothing and nothing.Today I find myself stuck for several days already. They ask me for documentation on where the money came from.Send the documents after only 1 hour from their block mail. To date, after 6 days no reply, I wrote again but still no answer.Poor and absurd service. Luckily I used it only for trivial things and I didn't rely on it.I remain convinced that REVOLUT treats its customers better and I advise everyone to abandon this useless and complicated platform.Here on Monese the customer is worth nothing, in fact the customer never receives answers. They only respond to reviews.

name: Erison Nascimento
title: Monese doesn't replay my email
content: I sent an email to Monese 3 days ago and I didn't receive any answer, M15173089

name: Birce
title: Horrible customer service
content: Horrible customer service, takes ages to get a response for a request. I guess asking for a debit card is the primary thing you could ever ask from your bank and should not take you weeks until you get it. I have been waiting for a single response for the last 5 days Monese. If replying takes so long, cannot imagine how long will it take me to receive the card, if it ever happens!

name: Vlad
title: AVOID!
content: First of all , no one even read in app chat , in few days they just drop your question . You can call them , but phone support is useless , all they can say is "We will escalate your case , wait for an E-mail ".September 18.2019 I've made a transaction of 56 ¬£ , UK to UK account , It was pending till October 29.2019 . I called them about ten times asking to cancel this transaction because I already paid to person with different account . Instead of resolve the issue they just suspended my account , (with money in it of course) . Send me nonsense questioning , Questions I already replied long time ago ..All those prepaid accounts companies have one excuse "We are FCA regulated company " , I wonder how did they get the license ..I strongly advice you DO NOT keep any money with any FCA regulated prepaid accounts companies . Unless you are ready to lose your money.This company exploiting trustpilot's reporting system to hide unwanted reviews ... draw your conclusions

name: Robert
title: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card‚Ä¶
content: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card issued by Sberbank Croatia and I cannot topup from my MasterCard issued by Sberbank Croatia. With both of them I can topup my revolut account/card.

name: Matteo Ricci
title: Conto bloccato / Blocked account
content: Mi hanno bloccato il conto dopo un anno che lo utilizzo davvero poco. In tutto ci ho fatto girare meno di 500 euro. Uso la carta solo per Pagare il parcheggio della mia auto. Praticamente poco e niente.Oggi mi ritrovo conto bloccato gi√† da diversi giorni. Mi richiedono documentazione sulla provenienza del denaro. Invio i documenti dopo solo 1 ora dalla loro mail di blocco. Ad oggi dopo 6 giorni nessuna risposta, ho scritto nuovamente ma ancora nessuna risposta.Servizio scadente e assurdo. Meno male che lo utilizzavo solo per cose futili e non ci ho fatto affidamento. Rimango dell'idea che REVOLUT tratta meglio i suoi clienti e consiglio a tutti di abbandonare questa inutile e complicata piattaforma. QUi su Monese il cliente non vale nulla, infatti il cliente non riceve mai risposte. Rispondono solo alle recensioni.****They blocked my account after a year that I use very little. In all, I made it run less than 500 euros. I only use the card to pay for parking my car. Virtually nothing and nothing.Today I find myself stuck for several days already. They ask me for documentation on where the money came from.Send the documents after only 1 hour from their block mail. To date, after 6 days no reply, I wrote again but still no answer.Poor and absurd service. Luckily I used it only for trivial things and I didn't rely on it.I remain convinced that REVOLUT treats its customers better and I advise everyone to abandon this useless and complicated platform.Here on Monese the customer is worth nothing, in fact the customer never receives answers. They only respond to reviews.

name: Erison Nascimento
title: Monese doesn't replay my email
content: I sent an email to Monese 3 days ago and I didn't receive any answer, M15173089

name: Birce
title: Horrible customer service
content: Horrible customer service, takes ages to get a response for a request. I guess asking for a debit card is the primary thing you could ever ask from your bank and should not take you weeks until you get it. I have been waiting for a single response for the last 5 days Monese. If replying takes so long, cannot imagine how long will it take me to receive the card, if it ever happens!

name: Andrew Donaldson
title: Taking over a week to process my‚Ä¶
content: Taking over a week to process my application? I don't think so - bye-bye Monese!
